               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500819-name-749" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-749" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-749" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-749" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PEARCE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer. On 13th July I was at Hammersmith with Gomm, who gave me a pair of trowsers to take to where we work—going up Hammersmith, I was <hi rend="italic">shoved</hi> off the pavement, and the trowsers snatched from under my arm—I did not see who it was—Eliza Godfrey ran after the person, and stopped him—I saw the prisoner afterwards, and asked him what made him snatch the trowsers from me—he said, "To take care of them"—I asked him to give me them—he said he would see me b—first—I called the police.</p>
               <p>
